Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.72,0:11:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,mean? People get ranked up. You know\Nwhat I'm saying? And then all the gar
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.04,0:11:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the the stuff that you put on yourself\Ngoes with that. You get to be the hunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.95,0:11:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So the theatrical glamorization is\Nseductive. Seductive. A lot of people
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.88,0:11:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,think they're very religious.\NThey've been seduced into the theater.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.80,0:12:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the theater of religiosity.\NThere's whole cultures, in fact, ones we
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.68,0:12:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,have Greek problems with, who are\Nseduced as a whole culture into the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.95,0:12:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,theater\Nof extreme religiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.04,0:12:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't help me.\NSomebody prostrates himself on the floor
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.56,0:12:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and then blows up my neighbors in the\Nbus. Save me all the frustration and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.07,0:12:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,have a little kindness and consideration\Nfor other human beings please. Thank
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.92,0:12:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you.\N>> That's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.80,0:12:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> All the theatrics doesn't mean anything.\NIt's racial. So the a true teacher
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.56,0:12:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,avoids that glamorization which is a\Nseduction. This is a seduction and it's
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.24,0:12:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,an explo exploitation of people. It's\Nputting a Hollywood twist on stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.92,0:12:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Materialistic truth is we don't need\Nworldly wealth. self-fulfilling
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.48,0:13:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,self doesn't need adherence followers\Ndoesn't want to sign up members
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.00,0:13:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,uh detached non-involvement in world\Naffairs
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.32,0:13:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,um I haven't marched in any parades\NI haven't carried any placards
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.72,0:13:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't intend to\Nthe world will have to save itself
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.32,0:13:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,mahari says\NThe world you think you see out there
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.24,0:13:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't even exist. It's a rejection\Nfrom your own perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.36,0:13:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And the best thing to do is to surrender\Nit to God. Surrender the world to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.80,0:13:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Uhhuh. Why? Because don't people don't\Neven know what the world is about. Why
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.16,0:13:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,would you want a medal in which you have\Nthis last idea what it's all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.00,0:13:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the purpose of human life in this\Nworld in the first place?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.12,0:13:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it to be Shambala? Is it to be a\Ncelestial realm?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.92,0:13:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There's supposed to be a celestial realm\Ncalibrated at 600. It's in another
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.44,0:14:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,dimension called heaven.\N>> No. The purpose of this world is I see
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.32,0:14:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,it. Let me see if what the way I'm\Nseeing is correct before I share it. The
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.72,0:14:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,way I'm seeing it is the way it is. Is\Nthis? Yes. Better be.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.83,0:14:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been counting on it, folks.\NPurpose of this world is maximum karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.76,0:14:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,opportunity.\NYou can expand here at a tremendous
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.76,0:14:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,rate. There are other dimensions, but\Nyou don't have a choice. What choices do
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.32,0:14:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you have in a celestial realm where\Neverybody's at 600? You got any choice?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.48,0:14:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> No.\N>> No. If everybody's heavenly and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.56,0:14:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,blissful, you're stuck in heavenly\Nblissful, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.44,0:14:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. After\N450,000 years, it dawns on you there's
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.12,0:15:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,some beyond celestial. Oh,\Nthere's some beyond 600. Okay. Now, the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.80,0:15:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,purpose of this dimension then is here.\NYou saw through the evolution of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.19,0:15:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness.\NThis is the place to maximize the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.88,0:15:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution of your consciousness. This is\Nthe most wonderful environment for
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.92,0:15:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,undoing negative karma and gaining\Npositive karma. This is the maximal
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.88,0:15:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,environment where you have every\Ngradation and every opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.16,0:15:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,where you're attracted by this and have\Nan aversion to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.12,0:15:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh this is the world of maximum\Nopportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.19,0:15:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,without walking into a battlefield of a\Nriddle of bullets for the sake of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.39,0:15:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,mother, country, wife, and children, for\Nthe sake of the king or whatever. How
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.92,0:15:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,are you going to cross over 200?\NHow are you going to cross over 200?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.04,0:15:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't do it just in your head. There\Ncomes the day when you got to walk into
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.51,0:16:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the bullets. I'm willing to die for what\NI believe. Bang. You're now over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.56,0:16:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,As I've said, women have done it for\Ngenerations through childbirth. The risk
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.95,0:16:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,of death from childbirth is extremely\Nhigh. How anybody even lived through it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.39,0:16:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to get the fourth or fifth? Well, my\Nfamily Bible, it goes back, you know, it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.95,0:16:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,always lists all the wives this guy had\Nand all the little children that that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.63,0:16:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you know the still births etc. So the\Nchance of getting of surviving child
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.56,0:16:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,birth was frankly very small child\Nfever, hemorrhage, eclampsia, all the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.00,0:16:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,things that we try to treat now. So the\Nwoman is facing almost you know very
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.36,0:16:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,likely death very if you get pregnant\Nenough times in the 17 1800s sooner or
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.83,0:16:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,later it'll get you. So after Mary she\Nsurvived three kids but the fourth one
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.72,0:16:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,put her under. Therefore the Bible Bible\Nsays that great uncle Henry then married
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.92,0:17:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the Katrina and she has but out of her\Nchildren how many died. So the woman
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.07,0:17:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,faces uh the fear of death uh in\Nchildhood in childbirth all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.16,0:17:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Traditionally the man has done it you\Nknow in war. So
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.60,0:17:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,this is a world of maximum karmic\Nopportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.43,0:17:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in war that you learn certain\Nthings that you cannot live outside of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.52,0:17:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,war. Unless you're actually facing\Nreally being blown up really really that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.72,0:17:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,bond that goes between you, your fellow\Nmates, your service to your country, the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.08,0:17:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,service to the queen, to the king, to\Nwhatever uh just can't happen
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.00,0:17:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you can actually literally\Nhemorrhage to death in childbirth. You
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.79,0:17:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,don't cross over for the sake of life,\Nfor the sake of this child, for the sake
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.12,0:17:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of this baby. You risk your life. You\Nhave to actually do it. The pain of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.79,0:18:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,childbirth is a real real real thing.\NMany of us have never been able to cross
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.91,0:18:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,these great barriers except by\Nidentification with mankind in general.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.24,0:18:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh Susan mentions during child birth\Nthat she thought of all all the women
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.72,0:18:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout all the time who were faced\Nwith this crisis and the fact that they
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.28,0:18:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,did it right gave you the power and the\Nstrength. I myself remember severe
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.03,0:18:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,conditions and I said\NI picture the civil war all these guys
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.32,0:18:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,laying on the battlefield with their leg\Nblown off this guy's hands blown off
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.00,0:18:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,this guy's face is just blown off.\NSomehow the human the human can
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.32,0:18:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,transcend that can handle it. So\Nthrough travail like the great tsunamis
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.24,0:19:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,let's say through great travail then we\Nbond with other others as humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.08,0:19:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise it's just a speech. All kinds\Nof jerks get up there and make peace
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.91,0:19:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,speeches and love and all that crap\Ndon't you why? Because that bonding has
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.72,0:19:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to be of the heart, you know, where we\Nwent to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.91,0:19:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,when we went to uh tattoo in Scotland. I\Nremember, you know, as a hundred bag
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.52,0:19:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,pipers come through all at once. The\Nscirrel, it just
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.72,0:19:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,does something just beyond the personal.\NAnd what is grabbed is the heart of
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.79,0:19:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,humanity.\NThe sound of the bagpipe at 510 or 520.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.16,0:19:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,When you hear that coming over the hill,\Nthe chill goes up your spine because
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.79,0:19:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,this is certain death walking. You\Nbetter win or you will die. Huh? So, but
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.76,0:19:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the courage to do that then comes from\Nthe bonding with all of humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.20,0:20:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We all bond with each other as humanity\Non an impersonal basis. And it's our
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.64,0:20:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,love for each other that goes out\Nthrough the heart of our oneness with
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.64,0:20:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,all humanity. That's what's lifts the\Nsea and all the prayer circles and all
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.76,0:20:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,are very good. But unless you feel that\Ncommonality of identification with all
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.84,0:20:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of mankind and all humankind, then you\Ncan't lift them. You can't lift the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.67,0:20:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,level of the sea. So on this coming day\Nwhen unity wants us all to pray
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.32,0:20:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,together, you know, that's what we do.\NSo you reaffirm your bonding
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.48,0:20:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,uh your love for mankind\Nwhich is like the collective heart of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.67,0:20:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind and the power of that collective\Nheart is what keeps us all surviving
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.60,0:20:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,because human life is extremely\Ndifficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.72,0:21:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Human life is extremely difficult.\NAnybody disagree?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.52,0:21:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. All right. So, all right. It it's\Nthen the owning the owning of the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.60,0:21:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,oneness of the heart of human humanness\Nitself. When we own that, we become
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.72,0:21:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that. We become the power of it. And\Nwhen we become the power of it, we have
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.28,0:21:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we have the power to transform it. You\Ncan't bring about peace without owning
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.55,0:21:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the heart of\Nhumanity as that who you are. So we'll
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.32,0:21:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,meet again later.\NWhat time do we
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.40,0:21:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So,\N>> well, we tried to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.24,0:21:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,um undemonize the ego so that you can be\Nfriendly with it, own it, and handle it
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.28,0:21:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,without riddling yourself with anxiety\Nand guilt and shame and despair and self
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.52,0:22:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,flagagillation,\Nwhich is why there's so few of
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.40,0:22:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightened people in the world.\NAnybody wants to plow through all that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.67,0:22:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Good God.\NOh yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.44,0:22:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We were talking about freedom of speech.\NFirst of all, it's overblown. It's not
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.36,0:22:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the highest calibration virtue that\Nthere is. Freedom of speech doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.91,0:22:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate, you know, like 900 something.\NTruth and integrity calibrates much
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.88,0:22:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,higher than free speech.\NThe downside of moral relativism is the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.12,0:22:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,abuse of free speech, you know,\Nand the decline through moral relativism
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.96,0:22:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of um the level of integrity in the\NUnited States is u part of the uh
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.64,0:22:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,judicial\Nactions.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.28,0:22:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The most uh important one was\Ninterpreting
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.72,0:23:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,uh\Nbehavior as symbolic speech. That was
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.32,0:23:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the ruling that took the bottom out.\NAll right. So if uh I forget what the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.20,0:23:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,exact um\Nuh court uh what what the what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.72,0:23:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody in the audience will probably\Nremember. But anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.79,0:23:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the ruling was\Num that the person's physical expression
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.20,0:23:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,behavior\Nwas symbolic speech and speech is
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.72,0:23:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,freedom. See?\N>> All right. So, if you interpret behavior
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.28,0:23:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,as symbolic speech, you just took the\Nbottom out of your society.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.96,0:23:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> All right. That means the Kucks clan is\Nokay, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.44,0:23:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,hanging black people. I mean, that's\Njust symbolic speech, isn't it? Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.72,0:23:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Burning crosses,\Nburning down black churches. I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.48,0:24:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that's just all symbolic speech, isn't\Nit?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.40,0:24:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you get what the downside of moral\Nrelativism is.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.64,0:24:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The other side of moral relativism is\Nits misunderstanding of egalitarianism.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.03,0:24:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Egalitarianism, which calibrates around\N265,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.44,0:24:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,then becomes the rationalization and\Nexcuse
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.48,0:24:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that all people are equal from an\Negalitarian viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.40,0:24:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankly, they ain't.\NThey aren't equal in this domain at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.52,0:24:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That people will just soon kill you as\Nlook at you. You know, you know, if
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.52,0:24:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to give a serial killer\Nequal rights with your local minister,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.40,0:24:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,then you're a little bit off in your\Nlittle bit off in the upper story. But
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.44,0:24:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the rationalization. See?\N>> All right. So, if action behavior then
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.03,0:25:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is symbolic speech and there's to be no\Nrestraint on speech, I can do anything I
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.96,0:25:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,want. Huh? And if there is no absolute\Nthen
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.24,0:25:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and no morality and no ethics. So in the\Nbook I call this you know the mad
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.44,0:25:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,hatter's tea party. I call it the\Nmorality of amorality.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.44,0:25:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They get out there and pontificate\Nagainst morality. That's the new
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.60,0:25:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,morality called amorality.\NAnd if you really want to understand it,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.00,0:25:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you read Herbert Marcus and you will see\Nwhy your kids that you sent to college
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.72,0:25:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,came home weird.\NAnd if you believe what that guy wrote,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.20,0:25:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,man, you are mental already\Nand somewhat deranged and programmed,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.40,0:25:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you know.\NSo moral relativism then is is a um
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.96,0:26:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,expressed in rhetoric and it's caused\Nmuch confusion in society. Equal
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.67,0:26:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,justice egalitarianism is the ideal.\NYes. But then under that ideal comes
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.20,0:26:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,behaviors that are beyond the pale. And\Nso you see the decline of freedom of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.08,0:26:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,speech.\NFree speech in the United States today.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.32,0:26:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say let's do\Nas a political concept calibrates over
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.52,0:26:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,260 265. All right. Free speech as\Nexercised in the United States today
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.20,0:26:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,through the media etc. calibrates over\N180 185 190 calibrates at 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.67,0:26:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,At best it's only 20 and something.\Nat 200 and something. I don't want to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.03,0:27:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,die for just for free speech.\NI mean, so some jerk can get up on a
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.84,0:27:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,soap box and blow off. I'm not going to\Nsacrifice my life for free speech. It
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.76,0:27:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates at 265. I mean, it's a\Nnicity,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.67,0:27:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's overheralded.\NThere are things more important than the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.64,0:27:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,libertineism of being able to spout off\Nany kind of malicious rhetoric you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.76,0:27:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,See,\NThat's my free speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.64,0:27:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> All is in divine order.\NWhere is the guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.20,0:27:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,>> He just looked over to you. That's why\Neverybody laughed.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.91,0:27:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> See if he's got a wristband on him.\NThose
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.52,0:28:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,suckers always gets in for free. Turns\Nhimself into a chipmunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.72,0:28:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All is in divine order. That's a good\Naffirmation to hold. All is in divine
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.96,0:28:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,harmony and all is in divine order. All\Nright. If all is in divine order, then
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.64,0:28:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the world is perfect as it is. Correct.\N>> Yeah. Right. All right. Uh otherwise
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.36,0:28:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,there'd be no point point to get born\Nhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.72,0:28:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If this was a celestial realm at 600,\Neverything was absolutely perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.84,0:28:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There'd be no purpose to human life. You\Ndon't need to incarnate to, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.32,0:28:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,find that out.\NUh so we forgot that was the word I
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.67,0:28:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,couldn't think of. Symbolic symbolic\Nspeech. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.88,0:28:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And um the third thing was\NI don't remember what the third thing
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.00,0:28:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,was now.\NI usually put down a couple of words of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.24,0:28:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,things I want to make sure to mention\Ntoday.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.44,0:29:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to handle the void though.\NThat's necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.15,0:29:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we're going to finish with the\Nslides. Or let's do the slides and then
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.52,0:29:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll get to the void. Okay. All right.\NUm, well, we did these already. I think
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.64,0:29:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,we did these. Didn't we do them?\N>> Y.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.67,0:29:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Uh,\Nlet's go back to the last slide. I want
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.96,0:29:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to make sure I did them.\N>> You did.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.64,0:29:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I mean, I don't want to lie in bed\Nsaying, "Gee, you didn't do the third
