Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.03,0:29:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Huh?\N>> This is the last slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.88,0:29:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh, okay.\N>> All right. So, you don't get
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.03,0:29:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,positionalized. You stay out of the uh\Nyou stay out of the political realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.32,0:29:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Equality\Nre is the irreverence for all of life
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.44,0:29:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's exherely\Navoid that which is dilotarious rather
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.76,0:29:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,than opposing it. So that's the\Nprinciple to be pro chocolate you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.24,0:30:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,have to be anti vanilla. In our current\Nsociety they think to be pro this you
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.08,0:30:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,got to be anti that.\Nuh non-temporal life is eternal and life
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.27,0:30:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot be destroyed. There is no such\Nthing as death. Death is an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.67,0:30:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We've done it many a time before\Naudiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.91,0:30:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And like\Nthe principle of the indestructibility
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.79,0:30:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of matter or of energy, for some reason,\Nmankind never noticed the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.67,0:30:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,indestructibility\Nof life itself. Right? Let's see. Life
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.00,0:30:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it cannot be destroyed. It is an\Nimpossibility. It is an impossibility
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.76,0:30:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,for death to occur. So stop worrying\Nabout it. Okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.36,0:30:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Non-temporal\Nand it's beyond proof. That which is
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.76,0:31:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,provable is within the linear Newtonian\Ndomain. Uh that which is of a higher of
